summary: This is a court subpoena issued by the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York to the Sacramento County Clerk/Recorder, commanding them to appear and produce a birth certificate for an unspecified individual in the case United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell. The subpoena is dated August 27, 2021, and demands appearance on November 29, 2021.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: The defendant in the criminal case United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell (20 Cr. 330 (AJN)), which is the subject of the subpoena.

persons.name: Audrey Strauss
persons.context: The United States Attorney for the Southern District of New York who signed and issued the subpoena.

events.title: Scheduled Court Appearance for Document Production
events.description: The Sacramento County Clerk/Recorder is commanded to appear in court to testify and produce a birth certificate for an unspecified individual related to the Ghislaine Maxwell case.

locations: 40 Foley Square, Courtroom 906, Borough of Manhattan, City of New York, New York
keyFacts: A federal subpoena was issued to compel the Sacramento County Clerk/Recorder to produce a birth certificate for an individual related to the Ghislaine Maxwell criminal case.
The subpoena indicates ongoing investigative or pre-trial evidence gathering by the U.S. Attorney's Office in the Maxwell case as of August 2021.
The identity of the individual whose birth certificate is sought is not specified in the provided text.
